{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"eb405d81-0729-42de-984a-d2d52c3cf781","content":"Here's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Replace** both it and the `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package with the single **`MSTest` v3** meta-package (which bundles the framework, adapter, and test SDK)\n\nYour test code (`using Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting`) stays the same — the namespace is unchanged in v3.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01HRrvQnG9e1C2qF8Vp5mf9a","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Upgrading to MSTest v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01SRtTuyowszqoehppyurE92","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-c8becce583a94adfa753564f3724fe9a/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.5.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-c8becce583a94adfa753564f3724fe9a/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"e1daec5a-f1fb-49ea-b87a-157ce7afd832","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .NET Framework test project that uses the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`. They want to upgrade to MSTest v3.\n\nHere's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove the assembly reference** to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add the MSTest v3 NuGet package** - MSTest v3 consolidated everything into a single `MSTest` package (replacing `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter`)\n3. **Update `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`** to a newer version (or it may no longer be needed with MSTest v3 since MSTest v3 uses `MSTest.Sdk` or includes the test SDK)\n\n\n4. **Check the target framework** - MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and above, so if the project targets `net462` or higher, it should be compatible.\n\nThe simplest approach is to use the `MSTest` meta-package version 3.x, which bundles the test framework, adapter, and SDK together, eliminating the need to manage multiple packages separately.\n\nSince MSTest v3 still uses the `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace, the actual test code won't require any changes. I could also consider using `MSTest.Sdk` as the project SDK for a more modern setup.","outputTokens":994,"requestId":"4C13:897A1:B51D84:DC7B50:6A014075"},"id":"712a0a32-041f-47f5-bc2d-ba4f363e40df","timestamp":"2026-05-11T02:35:50.565Z","parentId":"01801eb1-10ae-482e-a5db-f3416ca2169c"}
